    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Diagnostics Manual - Hard Start and No Start Diagnostics - Test Procedures - 7. Engine
        Systems
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s305010503.7" svcproctype="diagnose" graphiccount="1">
        <title>7. Engine Systems</title>
        <figure id="f305010522" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ31/J31118.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption></caption>
        </figure>
        <para id="tp305010507">
            <title>Purpose</title>To check engine systems for hard start or no start conditions
        </para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <title>Tools</title>
            <item>
                <para>Inspection lamp</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Wrench</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid personal injury, death, including damage to the engine or vehicle, read all safety
                    instructions in the "Safety Information" section of this manual.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check fuel supply system (including tanks, transfer pump, HFCM, and lines) for leaks and
                damage.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check engine for oil leaks.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect cooling system for leaks.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check sensor, relay, and control module connections. All connections must be seated, in good
                condition, and free of damage or corrosion.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The engine will not start if the following components are disconnected or damaged:</para>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Injection Pressure Regulator (IPR) valve</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Camshaft Position (CMP) sensor</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Crankshaft Position (CKP) sensor</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove cover from power distribution box, and check distribution box, glow plug relay, and
                IAH relay for corrosion.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check battery cable connections for corrosion. All connections must be seated, in good
                condition, and free of damage or corrosion.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check engine wiring harness for correct routing and protection against rubbing or
                chaffing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check air cleaner housing for damage or distortion that could allow unfiltered air into the
                engine.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check air induction system for leaks.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Unfiltered air will cause accelerated engine wear.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>If leaks in the air induction system are suspected, continue with step 10.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check for end seal movement inside the housing. End seal movement is indicated, if the seal
                contact area is polished. A polished contact area indicates that unfiltered air has passed by the filter
                element and into the engine.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check air cleaner element for end cap dents, holes, damaged seals, and soot.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check air intake hoses and clamps for tightness and positioning over sealing beads.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check the chassis mounted Charge Air Cooler (CAC) and piping.</para>
        </step1>
        <table id="t305010507" type="simple" frame="topbot">
            <title>Possible Causes</title>
            <tgroup cols="1" align="left">
                <colspec colname="col1"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry>
                            <para>Loose or leaking fuel supply lines could cause fuel system to lose prime.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry>
                            <para>Kinked or blocked fuel supply lines can restrict fuel flow.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry>
                            <para>Excessive fuel or oil leaks</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry>
                            <para>Coolant leaks could indicate serious engine damage.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry>
                            <para>Damaged, corroded or incorrectly installed electronic connectors</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry>
                            <para>Blockage in the air induction system</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
